<subSubSection id="9FECEF749A677CBE3E65158AD9B6CDD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="C5F2F2CE0BDCEFB90CAE45A07B3CB87A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62B6731D1D20D0E860BFC005DF83CB20" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Slender twining perennial with wiry whitish stems with flaky bark, reaching several metres in length, sometimes rooting at the nodes. Leaves petiolate, 2-8 
<normalizedToken id="8832FBFC87847B36FA4F471C28A0A5C5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-6 cm, lanceolate, acute and mucronate, base sagittate, cordate or subtruncate, the auricles up to 1 cm long, adaxially glabrous, abaxially paler, white-punctate, glabrous or puberulent; petioles 3-20 mm. Inflorescence of 1-5-flowered axillary cymes; peduncles 1.5-2 cm, often penetrating leaf sinus as in 
<taxonomicName id="150DC866C576421651AF4380A1737BC5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aristolochiifolia">
<emphasis id="3A24ECCBAB011F3D5BF5A62D5C392616" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. aristolochiifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; bracteoles scale-like, c. 1 mm long; pedicels 5-10 mm; sepals very unequal, oblong-elliptic to lanceolate, outer 2-5 
<normalizedToken id="830192007B9CA5E9304E200041B7C43E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, acute, inner 5-7 mm, rounded; corolla 3.5-4 cm long, funnel-shaped, gently flared from a slender base, white, glabrous, limb 3.5-4 cm diam., unlobed. Capsules ovoid, 8-9 
<normalizedToken id="BB3859DCBE5D6AE117C4AEBA2B028DFE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm; seeds 4, 4 
<normalizedToken id="C5F9E2341E2B2EA997F284975CA83E8B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, dark brown, puberulent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
